verbose_text: Insulin is capable of inducing anabolic responses that promote the synthesis of type II collagen and proteoglycan, inhibit expression of the collagenases, matrix metalloproteinase- (MMP-) 1 and 13, and a disintegrin and metalloproteinase with thrombospondin motifs (ADAMTS), and counteract the effects related to IL-1beta [XREF_BIBR].
